{"title":"All New Cannondale Synapse Neo Endurance e-Bike","link":"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-cannondale-synapse-neo-endurance-e-bike/","date":1712929432000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--1536x1007.jpeg\" width=\"1536\" height=\"1007\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo bike\" /></p>\n<p>The all-new Cannondale Synapse Neo brings high-performance road endurance to the e-bike crowd. The new e-bike hopes to channel the successful Cannondale Synapse endurance-focused road bike with a lightweight design and a Bosch power system. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"894\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--1536x894.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo full bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--1536x894.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--297x173.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--120x70.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--768x447.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-full-bike--2048x1192.jpeg 2048w\" /></a><figcaption>Images: Cannondale</figcaption></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The cornerstone of the new Cannondale e-bike line is the <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/bosch-performance-line-sx-ebike-motor/\" target=\"_blank\">Bosch Performance Line SX motor</a>, the brand’s lightest e-bike motor to date. However, those in the U.S. will see the faster Bosch Performance Line Sprint which provides assist up to 28mph. </p>\n\n\n\n<h2>Cannondale Synapse Neo – What’s New? </h2>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1019\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive--1536x1019.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo non drive\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive--1536x1019.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive--297x197.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive--120x80.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive--768x509.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-non-drive-.jpeg 1906w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The new Cannondale Synapse Neo takes the Synapse acoustic as a jumping-off point and tries to stay close to the original aesthetic. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1278\" height=\"1128\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo motor\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor-.jpeg 1278w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor--297x262.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor--120x106.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-motor--768x678.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The glaringly obvious (but not really that much) difference is the motor. Its Bosch Performance Line Sprint drive unit. This baby will do will do 28mph maxed out (US only – sorry Europe) and is said to maintain a natural pedaling feel. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"964\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen--1536x964.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo screen\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen--1536x964.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen--297x186.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen--120x75.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen--768x482.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-screen-.jpeg 1708w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The motor is smartly integrated into the carbon frame without drawing too much attention to the addition. The controls are neatly accessible to the rider via the top tube and a bar-mounted control. The Bosch head unit displays most motor operations, gear selection, and, most importantly, battery life. </p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1124\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo--1536x1124.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo--1536x1124.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo--297x217.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo--120x88.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo--768x562.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-.jpeg 1698w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>If you’re looking to extend said battery life. You can do so fairly easy with an additional PowerMore 250Wh add-on battery that mounts to the seat tube.</p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Series 2 Carbon</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"825\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--1536x825.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo bars\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--1536x825.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--297x160.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--120x64.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--768x413.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bars--2048x1100.jpeg 2048w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The frame screams Cannondale, with a sleek, dark color palette and dropped seat stays, similar to the SuperSix Evo. The carbon frame is lightweight, Cannondale Series 2 carbon.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"931\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter--1536x931.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo shifter\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter--1536x931.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter--297x180.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter--120x73.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter--768x465.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-shifter-.jpeg 1908w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cannondale gear rounds out the build by adding its Conceal Stem, HollowGram carbon wheels, and Shimano electronic shifting, keeping things clean and quick.</p>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1512\" height=\"1132\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header-.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo header\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header-.jpeg 1512w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header--297x222.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header--120x90.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-header--768x575.jpeg 768w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>For those who will use the Neo for commuting, it comes with mounts for a kickstand, fenders, and a rear rack. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Key Features – Cannondale Synapse Neo </h3>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Cannondale Series 2 Construction and proven endurance race geometry.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bosch Performance Line Sprint motor offers up to 55 Nm of torque and 600 watts of assist, all the way to 28mph.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Integrated 400Wh battery offers range for long rides, and keeps weight low.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Shimano’s Ultegra Di2 12-speed electronic drivetrain.</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Race-ready HollowGram R45 carbon wheels with 700x30c Vittoria tires </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Vision Metron Aero Carbon bars </li>\n\n\n\n<li>HollowGram 1 SAVE seatpost</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<h3>How About Sizing? </h3>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1007\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--1536x1007.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo bike\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--1536x1007.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--297x195.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--120x79.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike--768x503.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-bike-.jpeg 1822w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<p>A phrase you’ll often hear from Cannondale is “Proportional Response approach.” This idea sprawls across the Cannondale line, most recently in its <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/cannondale-scalpel-120-travel-front-and-rear/\">Scalpel XC Mountain bike</a>. The idea is that the bike is engineered for consistent performance across the size range. Every rider gets the same ride quality, handling, and responsiveness from the biggest to the smallest. </p>\n\n\n\n<h3>Synapse Neo Geometry</h3>\n\n\n\n<figure>\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"990\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2--1536x990.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo geo 2\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2--1536x990.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2--297x191.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2--120x77.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2--768x495.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-2-.jpeg 1812w\" /></a></figure>\n\n\n\n<figure><a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-.jpeg\"><img width=\"1536\" height=\"1080\" src=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo--1536x1080.jpeg\" alt=\"Cannondale Synapse Neo geo\" srcset=\"https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo--1536x1080.jpeg 1536w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo--297x209.jpeg 297w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo--120x84.jpeg 120w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo--768x540.jpeg 768w, https://bikerumor.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Cannondale-Synapse-Neo-geo-.jpeg 1852w\" /></a></figure>\n</figure>\n\n\n\n<h3>Cannondale Synapse Neo Build </h3>\n\n\n\n<p>The Synapse Neo arrives with a full Shimano Ultegra R8170 Di2 groupset and a 50/34t FSA Bosch crankset. You can find the full breakdown of the build below. </p>\n\n\n\n<ul>\n<li>Frame: Synapse Neo Carbon, Series 2 Carbon </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Fork: Synapse Neo Carbon, Series 2 Carbon </li>\n\n\n\n<li>Seatpost: HollowGram 1 SAVE seatpost</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Groupset: Shimano Ultegra Di2 8170, 12-speed</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Wheels: HollowGram R45 carbon wheels</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Tires: Vittoria Corsa, 30mm</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Gear ratios: 50/34t / 11-34t</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Bars: Vision Metron Aero carbon, 31.8</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Stem: Cannondale C1 Conceal, Alloy, 31.8, -6°</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Saddle: Fizik Tempo Argo R5</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Sizes: XS, S, M, L, XL</li>\n\n\n\n<li>Price:$8,500 / £6,000 / €8,499</li>\n</ul>\n\n\n\n<p>The Cannondale Synapse Neo will be available in shops May 2024 </p>\n\n\n\n<p><a href=\"https://www.cannondale.com/en-us/bikes/electric/e-road/synapse-neo\">Cannondale.com</a></p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com/all-new-cannondale-synapse-neo-endurance-e-bike/\">All New Cannondale Synapse Neo Endurance e-Bike</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://bikerumor.com\">Bikerumor</a>.</p>","author":"Jordan Villella","siteTitle":"Bikerumor","siteHash":"49f427af0a926f4232eb837006841d7242e153e3afbb590f32e4b104ea3e2718","entryHash":"7d19407bf84d4573768f7c51acea5ae67833a3f1d6dec607cc10f7fd7c484f09","category":"Cycling"}